    <unit id="extconf.additionalReadOnlyTables">
      <segment>
        <source>Additional read-only tables: comma-separated list of non-workspace-capable tables to expose for reads via MCP (e.g. sys_file). These cannot be written through workspace tools.</source>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="extconf.fileSandboxRoot">
      <segment>
        <source>MCP file sandbox root folder. Use a combined identifier such as &quot;1:/mcp/&quot;. This defaults to fileadmin/mcp/ in the default storage.</source>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="extconf.workspaceUploadSubfolders">
      <segment>
        <source>Store MCP uploads in workspace-specific subfolders below the sandbox root for safer draft handling.</source>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="extconf.allowMcpTokenInQueryString">
      <segment>
        <source>Allow passing the MCP bearer token as a query parameter (insecure: URLs are logged by proxies). Use only for legacy clients; prefer the Authorization header.</source>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="extconf.enableMcpAuthHeaderDiagnostic">
      <segment>
        <source>Enable the public ?test=auth diagnostic on the MCP endpoint (used by the backend connection check). Disable on hardened sites if you do not need it.</source>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="extconf.localUnsafeMode">
      <segment>
        <source>Local development mode: relax workspace-only writes, non-workspace table blocking, and the file sandbox so MCP can edit live records and write anywhere in fileadmin. &quot;auto&quot; detects DDEV and the TYPO3 development context. User TSconfig options.mcpServer.localUnsafeMode can override this; options.mcpServer.strictSandbox or feature flag mcpServer.strictSandbox forces strict mode. NEVER enable unsafe mode on production.</source>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="extconf.enforceCapabilityManifest">
      <segment>
        <source>Enforce the capability manifest (Configuration/Capabilities.yaml). Tools whose required capabilities are not declared/granted are rejected at call time. Disable only for debugging.</source>
      </segment>
    </unit>
